5|$|On 15 October 1944, Marinić filed {{charges against}} Pulherija and Gaudencija before the Land Commission for the Determination of Crimes by the Occupiers and Their Supporters. Pulherija fled to Austria {{before the end}} of the war, the only one of the nuns to do so. Gaudencija {{remained}} at the Children's Home, eventually moving to Ljubljana. No extradition of Pulherija was ever attempted, and neither nun was ever declared <b>a</b> <b>war</b> <b>criminal.</b> According to Fumić, the inhumane actions of Pulherija and other nuns and their role in the deaths of many children has never been condemned by the Catholic Church. Pulherija died in Austria in 1981.|$|E
